                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d894">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/33961: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-15T00:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 15, 1944—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received April 16—9
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>686. There has been no noticeable change of late in Anglo-Turk relations. The
                    British continue their attitude of aloofness which the Turks have now adopted in
                    their attitude towards the British. In conversation yesterday with the British
                    Ambassador he indicated that if the Turk Government responds in a cooperative
                    manner to the British and American notes on future trade between Turkey and
                    Germany an improvement in Anglo-Turk relations may result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
